Nia Parler, 41, was taken into custody by authorities in Montgomery County, Maryland overnight Saturday on charges she wheeled her quadriplegic son into woods in Philadelphia then went to visit her boyfriend in Maryland . 
  Police say she left the 21-year-old wheelchair-bound son in a wooded park with nothing but a blanket and a Bible on Monday morning . 
  He was found on Friday night lying 10 feet from his wheelchair . 
  Parler was arrested on charges including aggravated assault and neglect of a care-dependent person . 
  Her son is non-verbal and suffers from cerebral palsy . 
 